Invalid bundle for a DSSE-content envelope logged to Rekor v1 with the
experimental hashedrekord-over-DSSE encoding (kind=hashedrekord/0.0.1).
The DSSE envelope is valid in isolation but it is not the envelope that
was logged to Rekor: SHA256(PAE(envelope)) does not match the
hashedrekord entry's recorded `data.hash`.

Construction:
  1. Sign in-toto statement A as DSSE → bundle1 (happy-path source)
  2. Sign a different in-toto statement B as DSSE with the same key and
     same Fulcio-issued certificate → bundle2
  3. In bundle1, replace the dsseEnvelope and the RFC3161 timestamps with
     those from bundle2.

Signed against production Sigstore Public Good using the
sigstore-conformance/extremely-dangerous-public-oidc-beacon workflow
identity. No custom trusted_root.json is shipped; the test uses the
default production trust root.
